gobblin.runtime

Class LimitingExtractorDecorator<S,D>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.runtime.LimitingExtractorDecorator<S,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - output schema type
    D - output record type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Extractor<S,D>, Decorator, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class LimitingExtractorDecorator<S,D>
extends Object
implements Extractor<S,D>, Decorator
    A decorator class for Extractor that uses a Limiter on data record extraction.

    The fact that the Limiter is passed in as a parameter to the constructor LimitingExtractorDecorator(Extractor, Limiter, TaskState) (Extractor, Limiter, State)} (Extractor, Limiter)} means multiple LimitingExtractorDecorators can share a single Limiter or each individual LimitingExtractorDecorator has its own Limiter. The first case is useful for throttling at above the task level, e.g., at the job level.
